In your class `Binary_tree` you implement a `__str__` and `__repr__` function by calling `self.to_string_tree2(...)`. But you do this with `self.get_root`. Note that you forgot to *call* the function. You thus should add brackets. By using `self.get_root` itself, you pass a reference to the method as parameter to the function call.

You thus can fix this with: 

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;class Binary_tree:

    # &amp;hellip;

    def __str__(self):
        return self.to_string_tree2(self.get_root&lt;b&gt;()&lt;/b&gt;,0)

    def __repr__(self):
        return self.to_string_tree2(self.get_root&lt;b&gt;()&lt;/b&gt;,0)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

